cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DM, cs.CV 

The paper introduces a new type of Tsetlin Machine for regression problems, which is a machine learning algorithm used for pattern recognition and classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm on different datasets, which suggests that it could fall under cs.DM (Data Mining) as well. Finally, the paper mentions the use of the algorithm for image classification, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
